The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, January 28, 2004 				 Zee Tele net jumps 65% to Rs 37 crore
 OUR BUREAU				 	 Chandra: Good tidings																								Mumbai, Jan. 27: Zee Telefilms has recorded a 65 per cent rise in its net profit at Rs 36.75 crore in the third quarter of the current fiscal compared with Rs 22.19 crore in the same period last year. 																								Total income of the media major increased from Rs 141.13 crore in the previous year to Rs 179.2 crore in the reporting period.																								On a consolidated basis, the group has posted a net profit of Rs 90.19 crore for the quarter compared with Rs 70.88 crore in the previous year, a rise of 27 per cent. Total income of Zee Telefilms increased from Rs 325.02 crore last year to Rs 389.43 crore in the reporting period.																								The company said the business environment is showing promises for advertising revenues, which is dependent on macro-economic factors and business confidence of the major advertiser groups. The company is confident about the continued expansion in subscription revenues as well, it added.																								Zee Telefilms added the uplinking of Zee Cinema and Zee TV from India would allow it to tap into the lucrative non-exporter advertising market.																								While ASC Enterprises, an Essel group company has launched the direct-to-home (DTH) services from October 2, Zee said its television channels are being marketed as part of the DTH bouquet. 																								Five new channels have been launched by Zee for the DTH bouquet, including action cinema, Classic Cinema, Premiere Cinema, FX and Smile TV.																								Zee Telefilms chairman and managing director Subhash Chandra said, The third quarter witnessed a recovery in advertising business, growing 7.7 per cent from Rs 171 crore to Rs 184.2 crore. This is in line with our expectations. Our subscription-based businesses also continued to grow, despite uncertainties on conditional access system. Crompton Greaves																								Crompton Greaves Ltd has posted a substantial rise in its net profit at Rs 15.94 crore for the third quarter ended December 31, 2003 as against Rs 3.44 crore in the same period last fiscal.																								The net income for the reporting quarter also grew to Rs 399.73 crore from Rs 366.05 crore in October-December 2002. 
